  412|  33.6k|fn logical_expr<'q>(q: &'q str, ctx: ParseCtx) -> IResult<&'q str, LogicalExpr, InternalParseError<'q>> {
  413|       |    // This is the most involved part of the parser, as it is inherently recursive.
  414|       |    //
  415|       |    // There are two sources of recursion here: parentheses introduce recursion,
  416|       |    // since the rule is simply '(' filter_expression ')'; and the boolean combinations
  417|       |    // require checking for an operator, and if any is present recursively parsing
  418|       |    // another filter and wrapping the result in an appropriate node type.
  419|       |    //
  420|       |    // In total, we handle the negation operator at the start and then apply the rules:
  421|       |    // - '(' |=> filter_expression, ')'
  422|       |    // - literal |=> comp_op, comparable
  423|       |    // - query, comp_op |=> comparable
  424|       |    // - query
  425|       |    // where |=> means a cut. We separately apply two additional restrictions:
  426|       |    // - negation cannot immediately precede a comparison,
  427|       |    // - query in a comparison must be singular.
  428|       |    // It would be possible to directly disallow them by the rules, but if the parser understands
  429|       |    // these two special cases it can give much clearer error messages about them.
  430|       |    //
  431|       |    // At the end, we check for `&&` and `||``, recurse and wrap if needed; if not, we end parsing
  432|       |    // and leave the rest to the parsers higher up the stack. They might accept the next
  433|       |    // character (e.g. it's `)` called from a recursive filter call, `,` chaining selectors,
  434|       |    // `]` ending a segment...) and are responsible for error handling otherwise.
  435|       |    #[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]
  436|       |    enum BooleanOp {
  437|       |        And,
  438|       |        Or,
  439|       |    }
  440|       |
  441|  33.6k|    let Some(ctx) = ctx.increase_nesting() else {
  442|     63|        return Err(Err::Failure(InternalParseError::RecursionLimitExceeded));
  443|       |    };
  444|       |
